Class HillbilliesTaskLangBaseVisitor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
      • hillbillies.part3.programs.internal.generated.HillbilliesTaskLangBaseVisitor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the visit operation. Use Void for operations with no return type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    HillbilliesTaskLangVisitor<T>, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParserVisitor, SelectedChecker

    public class HillbilliesTaskLangBaseVisitor<T>
extends org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
implements HillbilliesTaskLangVisitor<T>
    This class provides an empty implementation of HillbilliesTaskLangVisitor, which can be extended to create a visitor which only needs to handle a subset of the available methods.
